25/11/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The House of Representatives approved Sadik Ahmetovic as the country's new security minister on Tuesday (November 24th). Ahmetovic, nominated by his Muslim Party of Democratic Action (SDA), will replace Tarik Sadovic, who was dismissed in July at the SDA's suggestion for obstructing some deportations of Islamic radicals. (RTRS, BHRT, Fena, Dnevni Avaz, Pincom - 24/11/09)
